text: The Tibetan bubble-nest frog or tubercle shrub frog (Pseudophilautus cavirostris) is a frog. It lives in Sri Lanka. The adult male frog was 17.4 mm long from nose to rear end. Scientists are not sure why these frogs all died. They think it was human beings changed the places where the frog lived. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Pseudophilautus cavirostris
